phoenixfs
---------
A Git-like filesystem implemented in userspace (using FUSE). Uses
packfile v3 for storing revision information.

Dependencies
------------
0. Git
1. Zlib (>= 1.2)
2. FUSE (>= 2.6)
3. pkg-config (>= 0.25)
4. Linux kernel (>= 2.6.15)

Usage
-----
For the first run, you need two directories:
1. A git directory where the data will be stored.  You need to `git
init` in the directory.
2. An empty directory to use as the mountpoint.

  $ cd /tmp
  $ mkdir gitdir mountpoint
  $ cd gitdir
  $ git init
  $ cd ..
  $ phoneixfs mount gitdir mountpoint

Use the mountpoint as you see fit.  Data will be written to the gitdir
on umount: you can use it for subsequent mounts.
